  "http://schema.org/description": "Colocalization Colormap –an ImageJ Plugin for the Quantification and Visualization of Colocalized SignalsThis ImageJ plugin implements the Jaskolski's algorithm (Jaskolski et al. 2005). It creates a pseudo-color map of correlations between pairs of corresponding pixels in two original input images. With it one can quantitativly visualize colocalization.",
